# Portfolio V4 — Comprehensive Codebase Audit Report

> [!NOTE]
> This is a detailed line-by-line architectural and technical audit of the **Niranjan S S Portfolio V4**. This document is intended for AI agents and human developers to understand the structural, architectural, and visual mechanics of the codebase without needing to read every file manually.

## 1. Global Architecture & Tech Stack

The application is a Single Page Application (SPA) built for extreme performance and cinematic visual fidelity.

- **Core Framework**: React 19 + TypeScript 6
- **Build Tool**: Vite 8
- **Styling**: Vanilla CSS Modules with strict CSS variables for the design system.
- **Animations**: GSAP 3.15 (Timeline, ScrollTrigger, quickTo)
- **Smooth Scrolling**: Studio Freight Lenis (1.3)
- **CMS / Data Layer**: Sanity v3 (Headless CMS)
- **Deployment**: Vercel (Frontend) + Sanity Cloud (Backend)

---

## 2. Core Application Orchestration

### `src/main.tsx`
The standard React entry point. Wraps the app in `<StrictMode>` and `<SanityProvider>`.

### `src/App.tsx`
The orchestrator of the entire experience. 
- **Lenis Setup**: Initializes `Lenis` for smooth scrolling using `requestAnimationFrame`. Syncs Lenis scroll events with `ScrollTrigger.update`.
- **Dynamic Routing**: There is no React Router. Instead, it uses a `COMPONENT_MAP` and renders sections sequentially based on the `siteSettings.sectionOrder` array fetched from Sanity.
- **Intersection Observer**: Tracks which section is currently in view (`activeSection`) and updates the `AmbientLighting` engine.
- **Achievement Tracking**: Tracks when a user scrolls through every trackable section to unlock the `Explorer` achievement.

### `src/index.css` (The Design System)
A master class in CSS custom properties and modular scaling.
- **Typography**: Uses `Outfit` (Display) and `Inter` (Body). Uses a perfect fourth modular scale (`--text-xs` to `--text-6xl`).
- **Spacing**: Uses `clamp()` for fluid spacing (`--space-section`, `--pad`).
- **Colors**: Deep blacks (`#050505`, `#0a0a0a`), minimal grays for text, and strict 4% usage of Indigo (`--accent: #6366f1`) and 1% Amber (`--warm: #f59e0b`).
- **Performance**: Strict use of `content-visibility: auto` and `contain-intrinsic-size` on sections to skip rendering off-screen content.

